\f1\fs28 \cf2 A novel feature of the Wheatstone system was the use of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bipolar_encoding"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 bipolar encoding}}. That is, both positive and negative polarity voltages were used. Bipolar encoding has several advantages, one of which is that it permits {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duplex_(telecommunications)"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 duplex}} communication. The Wheatstone tape reader was capable of a speed of 400 words per minute.\
